🆕 Missed / Extra Commands Added in RHEL 10
The rhc connectivity stack on RHEL 10 relies on a brand new Feature Level architecture to replace granular flag choices. [1, 2]
• Register with a specific Feature Level:
rhc connect --activation-key=<key> --organization=<org> --feature-level=<level>
(Available Levels: remote-management [Default], analytics, or content-only to restrict cloud visibility).
• Check the active feature configuration state:
rhc status
• Toggle specific cloud capabilities post-registration:
rhc enable <feature> or rhc disable <feature>
• Inspect explicit RHEL 10 Product Signing roots:
rct cat-cert /etc/pki/product-default/<product_id>.pem (Used heavily in RHEL 10 to check architecture compatibility bounds)
