5. System Purpose Configuration
System purpose lets you tag RHEL machines by their deployment footprint so your organization can automatically categorize resource usage graphs in the cloud console
• View system purpose settings:
subscription-manager syspurpose show
• Set OS Role: Tag the server role (e.g., Server, Workstation).
subscription-manager syspurpose role --set="Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server"
• Set SLA/Support level: Define your support coverage requirements.
subscription-manager syspurpose service-level --set="Standard"
• Set Usage type: Classify environment footprints (Production, Development, QA).
subscription-manager syspurpose usage --set="Production"
